Sentencas: The electrolyte supported cells with the La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-delta (LSTF0.7)-CeO2|ScSZ (scandia-stabilized zirconia)|La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-delta-CeO2 symmetrical configuration are fabricated by infiltration method and investigated as reversible solid oxide cells (RSOCs) at different CO/CO2 ratios.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: A well-deposited microstructure is observed in the infiltrated electrode.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: From the I-V curves, the maximum current density of 1.90 A cm(-2) at 2.0 V is obtained for CO: CO2 ratio of 1: 1 for CO2 electrolysis at 850 degrees C, while the corresponding power density under the same conditions is 357 mW cm(-2) in fuel cell mode.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) is conducted for better understanding the electrode catalytic mechanism.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The whole symmetrical cell achieves the polarization resistance (R-p) values of 0.284 and 0.203 V cm(2) at 850 degrees C under open circuit and at 1.4 V, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Under reversible operation (cyclic voltammetry) at 800 degrees C, no distinct degradation is found in the cell with the infiltrated LSTF0.7 symmetrical electrodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The long-term stability at 1.2-2.0 V characterized by potentiostatic measurement indicates that the prepared LSTF0.7-CeO2 composite electrode is comparatively stable at low voltages while a degradation behavior is observed at high voltages.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: These results illustrate that the LSTF0.7-CeO(2)composite is a promising active ceramic electrode for symmetrical RSOCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of highly active ceramic symmetrical electrode La0.3Sr0.7Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-δ-CeO2 for reversible solid oxide cells
